    {
      "parameters": {
        "jsCode": "// items = array of workflow items n8n gives this node automatically\n// Each item has .json.lesson_text\n\nreturn items.map(item => {\n  let text = (item.json.lesson_text || '').toString();\n\n  // Clean & shrink text\n  text = text\n    .replace(/\\r?\\n+/g, ' ')\n    .replace(/\\s+/g, ' ')\n    .replace(/\\[.*?\\]\\(.*?\\)/g, '')\n    .replace(/[#*_`>~=-]/g, '')\n    .trim();\n\n  return {\n    json: {\n      ...item.json,\n      safe_text: text,\n    }\n  };\n});\n"
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.code",
      "typeVersion": 2,
      "position": [
        1008,
        32
      ],
      "id": "fcc8bf0a-6c0b-4f3a-a9f1-11b19f1b9809",
      "name": "Prepare Lesson Text"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "promptType": "define",
        "text": "=You are a data-science tutor and expert Python instructor. Your task is to read the lesson_text and generate clear, correct answer explanations that summarize key concepts. These answers will later be used to create quiz questions. \n\nYou MUST respond with a single valid JSON object and nothing else.\n\nSchema:\n\n{\n  \"lesson_text\": \"<string (MUST COPY EXACTLY from input, character-for-character)>\",\n  \"answers\": [\n    {\n      \"answer\": \"<string (exact, concise explanation from lesson_text)>\",\n      \"difficulty\": 1 | 2 | 3,\n      \"category\": \"concept_check\" | \"definition\" | \"application\"\n    }\n  ]\n}\n\nRules:\n\n1. Copy lesson_text EXACTLY as received; do not modify, summarize, or truncate it. \n2. Use ONLY information present in lesson_text; do NOT add or infer content. \n3. Produce **4–6 answers**. Each answer must be concise, beginner-friendly, and factually accurate. \n4. Do NOT write questions; only generate answer explanations. \n5. Each answer must include:\n   - difficulty: 1 for basic, 2 for intermediate, 3 for advanced\n   - category: one of \"concept_check\", \"definition\", or \"application\"\n6. Do not include any extra text, markdown, or code fences. Output must be valid JSON.\n\nLesson Content:\n\"{{ $json.lesson_text }}\"\n",
        "batching": {}
      },
      "type": "@n8n/n8n-nodes-langchain.chainLlm",
      "typeVersion": 1.7,
      "position": [
        1504,
        32
      ],
      "id": "4bc8e248-0854-4503-a49c-acc119f5254e",
      "name": "LLM Chain - Answer Generation1"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "promptType": "define",
        "text": "=You are a data-science tutor.\nYou must NOT rewrite, summarize, modify, or replace the lesson_text.\nYou must NOT introduce any concepts that do not already appear in the input.\nYou must STRICTLY produce JSON following the schema below.\n\nYou MUST treat all input values as literal truth.\nIf something is missing or unclear, do NOT invent content. Simply use what is present.\n\nOutput a single JSON object with this schema:\n\n{\n  \"lesson_text\": \"<string> (MUST COPY EXACTLY from input, character-for-character)\",\n  \"qa_pairs\": [\n    {\n      \"question\": \"<string ending with '?'>\",\n      \"answer\": \"<string (exact copy of the input answer)>\",\n      \"difficulty\": 1 | 2 | 3,\n      \"category\": \"concept_check\" | \"definition\" | \"application\"\n    }\n  ]\n}\n\n\nRules:\n\nlesson_text must be copied EXACTLY as received.\n\nFor each input answer, generate exactly ONE question.\n\nThe answer in each qa_pair MUST be copied verbatim.\n\ndifficulty and category must be copied verbatim.\n\nThe question must be based ONLY on the answer. Not the lesson text.\n\nGenerate the SAME number of qa_pairs as answers.\n\nYour response MUST be valid JSON with no Markdown, no code fences, no explanations.\n\nIf the input includes 4 answers, output 4 qa_pairs.\n\nInput:\n\n{{ JSON.stringify($json.parsedAnswers) }}",
        "batching": {}
      },
      "type": "@n8n/n8n-nodes-langchain.chainLlm",
      "typeVersion": 1.7,
      "position": [
